0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/6-wordpress-plugins-for-higher-website-conversions/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/1-1.jpg\" width=\"852\" height=\"480\" title=\"6 WordPress plugins for higher website conversions\" alt=\"6 WordPress plugins for higher website conversions\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">WordPress rules the web, accounting for 33% of the online website market share according to a 2019 survey by w3techs.com. That&#8217;s up from 25% in 2015. Chances are, if you are an online seller, you are using WordPress to power to your ecommerce store. If you are looking to increase your traffic and supercharge your [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/6-wordpress-plugins-for-higher-website-conversions/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Whitney Blankenship\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5908:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/6-wordpress-plugins-for-higher-website-conversions/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/1-1.jpg\" width=\"852\" height=\"480\" title=\"6 WordPress plugins for higher website conversions\" alt=\"6 WordPress plugins for higher website conversions\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>WordPress rules the web, accounting for 33% of the online website market share according to a 2019 survey by w3techs.com. That&#8217;s up from 25% in 2015. Chances are, if you are an online seller, you are using WordPress to power to your ecommerce store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are looking to increase your traffic and supercharge your conversion rates, we have some must-have <a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/\">WordPress plugins</a> to share with you. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>6 WordPress Plugins that Will Help You Increase Conversions and Drive Traffic to Your WordPress Site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h1>1. Omnisend</h1>\n\n\n\n<p>We always like to start with the best. Omnisend&#8217;s <a href=\"https://www.omnisend.com/blog/exit-intent-popup-examples-small-online-businesses/\">popup form</a> and marketing technology integrate seamlessly with WooCommerce, the most popular ecommerce plugin for WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Omnisend integration, you can use the data collected in your WooCommerce store to</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Segment your customers by demographics and buying habits</li><li>Automate your marketing to increase conversion rates and revenue</li><li>Reduce cart abandonment and capture more sales</li><li>Increase the amount per transaction by automatically up-selling customers</li><li>Reactivate customers who haven&#8217;t shopped in a while</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see why Omnisend is our number one choice for WordPress plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h1>2. Hello Bar</h1>\n\n\n\n<p>A popup form is excellent for attracting interest in your brand and increasing sales, but eventually, it slips away out of the sight of your customers. Hello Bar, on the other hand, is an ever-present tool to remind customers of your most important offers or details. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can integrate Hello Bar with your favorite email management system, use it to direct customers to a particular page on your ecommerce site, or make an announcement like Free Shipping. </p>\n\n\n\n<h1>3. WP Health</h1>\n\n\n\n<p>Nothing can destroy conversion rates and your reputation like downtime and friction. It is vital to keep track of your website&#8217;s performance at all times. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why we love WP Health. This plugin allows you to monitor the health of your site 24/7. WP Health alerts you if</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Your site is down</li><li>Another site has blacklisted your store</li><li>You have plugin vulnerabilities</li><li>There are broken images on your site</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, you can keep track of how fast your site is loading and so much more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>WP Health is a must-have plugin if you want to keep conversions up and revenue coming in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h1>4. Yoast</h1>\n\n\n\n<p>Traffic plus conversion equals revenue. A simple way to drive product sales is by increasing website traffic. SEO is the organic way to get traffic to your ecommerce store, and Yoast is the number one recommended SEO tool for WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With their free or premium version, you can begin increasing website traffic with little or no SEO skills. Yoast will make recommendations in your content until it gives you the green light on SEO and readability. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yoast will suggest and track </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Keyword or key-phrase density</li><li>Meta descriptions</li><li>Optimal title lengths</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>and so much more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO has never been easier. This plugin is a must have for website traffic and conversions. </p>\n\n\n\n<h1>5. Social Share</h1>\n\n\n\n<p>Social media sharing is one of the most significant ways to drive traffic to your storefront so that you can increase conversions. According to Hubspot, customers are 71% more likely to purchase if a friend has referred them on social media. This truth makes Social Sharing one of the most significant ways to drive high-converting traffic to your storefront.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Social Share is a platform that makes it super simple for customers to share your products with their friends through</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Email</li><li>Facebook</li><li>Instagram</li><li>Pinterest</li><li>Google Plus</li><li>LinkedIn</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>and more. </p>\n\n\n\n<h1>6. Referral Candy</h1>\n\n\n\n<p>Since we already know that referrals boost conversions, why not give your customers a reason to share with their friends? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Referral Candy, you can offer your customers discounts, store credits, cash payouts or tangible gifts in response to sharing your products with their friends. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Referral Candy is a customer referral plugin that runs on autopilot once it is set up on your WordPress ecommerce site. The software tracks everything. All you have to do is watch it bring in more sales. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" />\n\n\n\n<p>There are tons of WordPress plugins out there for ecommerce, and sifting through them all can be time consuming. Hopefully, this article is a good launching point for you to find the right plugins for your store. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have a WordPress ecommerce store, we hope these six plugins will take your conversions and revenue to the next level.</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/6-wordpress-plugins-for-higher-website-conversions/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/6-wordpress-plugins-for-higher-website-conversions/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"Creating a Profitable Affiliate Website with WordPress At Home\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/creating-a-profitable-affiliate-website-with-wordpress-at-home/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/creating-a-profitable-affiliate-website-with-wordpress-at-home/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 17 Apr 2019 18:39:04 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Introducing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"affiliate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"create\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"wordpress development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=416061\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1294:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/creating-a-profitable-affiliate-website-with-wordpress-at-home/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wordpress-1084758_1280.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"Creating a Profitable Affiliate Website with WordPress At Home\" alt=\"Creating a Profitable Affiliate Website with WordPress At Home\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">Affiliate programs are extremely popular on the web and is an easy way to get started on the web, for both producers of products and product promoters. It has a low cost of entry, and low risk, as you only pay for products sold whilst expanding your reach, and product promoters have no need to [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/creating-a-profitable-affiliate-website-with-wordpress-at-home/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sonia Bell\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8245:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/creating-a-profitable-affiliate-website-with-wordpress-at-home/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wordpress-1084758_1280.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"Creating a Profitable Affiliate Website with WordPress At Home\" alt=\"Creating a Profitable Affiliate Website with WordPress At Home\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>Affiliate\nprograms are extremely popular on the web and is an easy way to get started on\nthe web, for both producers of products and product promoters. It has a low\ncost of entry, and low risk, as you only pay for products sold whilst expanding\nyour reach, and product promoters have no need to produce or store the stock\nthey are selling.<br>\nWhat is an\nAffiliate Business? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Affiliate marketing is a common and profitable\nbusiness model on the internet ‚Äì where you essentially recommend products,\nservices or offers from other businesses by linking to them on your site. A\npurchase will be picked up via the code embedded in the affiliate link for your\ncommission to be paid.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Pros:<ul><li>You can\nearn money practically as you sleep, from anywhere and at any time</li></ul><ul><li>Very low\ninvestment cost</li></ul><ul><li>No need for\ne-commerce infrastructure maintenance</li></ul><ul><li>No need for\nproducts ‚Äì you promote other‚Äôs products</li></ul></li><li>Cons<ul><li>You still\nneed to work to make this work!</li></ul><ul><li>You only\nget paid if there is a purchase, so you need a website, following, traffic and\nactual purchase conversions</li></ul><ul><li>Commissions\nvary ‚Äì high traffic volumes required to make good money.</li></ul></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why\nUse WordPress?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Used by around 75 million websites, WordPress\nis by far the most popular open source Content Management System in the world ‚Äì\nhighly customizable and flexible, free to install with thousands of templates\nand plugins. They have developed stunning purpose-built themes for Affiliate\nMarketing, which makes it easy to publish product images or videos,\nprofessional looking reviews, product comparisons, star ratings and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Choose a Niche</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Different types of affiliate websites are\navailable, such as affiliate niche blogs, authority blogs, daily deals, price\ncomparisons or product reviews. Pick your niche carefully in a market you are\nfamiliar with. A niche refers to a small, specialized section of the market.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Choose Your Products and\nAffiliate Partners</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have chosen the niche products you\nwant to promote, you can look at the footer of their websites to see which\naffiliate marketing programs they use, or you may want to look at the big\naffiliate marketing programs such as AWIN, Amazon Associates, ShareASale, and\nothers to see what products are available and pick from there, once you have\njoined. You may want to find independent companies who offer their own\naffiliate programs that operate in the niche market you are passionate about.<br>\n<strong>WordPress Affiliate Site Builder\nThemes </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you are starting out it is better to go\nwith a versatile theme like Total Responsive Multi-Purpose WP Theme, as you are\nmore likely to succeed if you choose a purpose-built affiliate theme. WordPress\nAffiliate themes, apart from the crucial basics, are responsive with a wealth\nof customizations and plugins. Some of the most popular ones include </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>REHub, which includes a few affiliate\nplugins and is extremely flexible.</li><li>Compare, with a minimal design that lets\nproducts take center stage.</li><li>SteadyIncome, one of the fastest loading themes from the MyThemeShop\nteam, very customizable and fully mobile ready.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Useful Tools and Plugins </h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Affiliate Link Plugins ‚Äì a very popular plugin\nis ThirstyAffiliates\n(categorization of affiliate networks, allows for easy insert, cloak links and\nauto-insert links with performance tracking). AffiliateWP creates fully self-hosted programs.</li><li>Review Plugins ‚Äì reviews are a great way to\nbuild trust in products if they are authentic. Some examples include Rich Reviews (rich snippets, ability to\nmoderate), WP Review (star, point, and percentage), WP Product Review Lite (allows your customers to add reviews) and AllinoneSchema.org\nRich Snippets (allows you to mark your reviews for\nGoogle).</li><li>Coupon Plugins ‚Äì daily deals can be generated\nwith Magic WP Coupons or Coupon\nCreator</li><li>Email Plugins ‚Äì converting visitors to mail\nsubscribers is very important and can be done with MailChimp, OutreachPlus (which has\nsome powerful mail management features) and Constant Contact (beginner friendly). </li><li>Content tools ‚Äì <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-rss-aggregator/\">WP RSS Aggregator</a> will\nautomatically fetch content from affiliate sites and even create auto-blogs.</li><li>Data review tools ‚Äì <a href=\"https://www.google.com/webmasters/tools/\">Google\nWebmaster Tools</a> and <a href=\"http://www.google.com/analytics\">Google\nAnalytics</a></li><li>Pop-up solutions &#8211; OptinMonster is one of the best out there.</li><li>SEO tools ‚Äì Yoast SEO will force you to choose a keyword when you publish and is\na must-have for every site</li><li>No follow tool ‚Äì Rel\nNofollow Checkbox lets you mark links as no-follow\nlinks.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><br>\n<strong>Setting Up Affiliate Links on Your\nWordPress Site</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sonia Bell, a marketing expert at <a href=\"https://www.smartpillwiki.com/best-solution-to-help-mental-focus-over-the-counter-pills-online/\">SmartPillWiki </a>says that ‚Äúthe easiest way to set up affiliate links on your website is through the Thirsty Affiliates plugin. Purchase a plan at their website, install the plugin and activate it. You can use the plan on multiple websites and the premium plan includes the auto-loader feature discussed above‚Äù.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now simply load your affiliate links in the\napp or use the link in the editor screen to bring up a pop-up for adding.<br>\n<strong>Create Free Content to Encourage More\nAffiliate Sales</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating free content that is useful, relevant\nand of interest is the best way to keep customers coming back to your site,\nwhether it is a blog, product reviews or any other format of affiliate\nmarketing. Your content must be of the highest caliber and meet the customer‚Äôs\nneeds and must fit the theme of your blog. Do your research, make sure your\ncontent is well structured and written professionally. Content must fit the\nproducts that you are promoting. Telling a story is a popular way of creating\ninteresting content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Reviews of products must be authentic for them\nto trust your reviews in the future and to become returning and referring\ncustomers.&nbsp; If you write glowing reviews\nfor sub-par products your customers will flee before you can blink an eye.\nEnsure that your SEO is set up properly and use plugins to assist you with\nSEO‚Äôs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Conclusion</strong><br>\nSetting up an affiliate marketing website or blog with WordPress is a great way\nto create passive income. It has low overhead, very low upfront investment cost\nand if you do your homework and plan it properly, you can create recurring\nincome streams with some initial hard work and dedication and minimal ongoing\nmaintenance. WordPress has simplified affiliate marketing to the point where\nnon-technical people can concentrate on producing the best content in that niche\nand let the themes and plugins do the rest. Don‚Äôt forget to disclose your\naffiliates as required by the FTC when promoting in the USA.</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/creating-a-profitable-affiliate-website-with-wordpress-at-home/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/creating-a-profitable-affiliate-website-with-wordpress-at-home/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:25:\"https://oceanwp.org/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"\n	hourly	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0